SIMPLE: successive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Successive
<hw>Suc*ces"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>successif</ets>. See <er>Succeed</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Following in order or in uninterrupted course; coming after without
interruption or interval; following one after another in a line or
series; consecutive; <as>as, the <ex>successive</ex> revolution of
years; the <ex>successive</ex> kings of Egypt; <ex>successive</ex>
strokes of a hammer.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Send the <qex>successive</qex> ills through ages down.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having or giving the right of succeeding to an
inheritance; inherited by succession; hereditary; <as>as, a
<ex>successive</ex> title; a <ex>successive</ex> empire</as>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Successive induction</b></col>. <fld>(Math.)</fld>
<cd>See <er>Induction</er>, 5.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Successively</ent>⟦br⟧
